Dear Young Scholar Families,

We are proud to be completing the first week of remote learning successfully today. YSGA would like to thank all students and families for making the best effort to log in every day. We also would like to send out a special thank you to our dedicated teachers for all the good work.

Please note that Monday, September 7, 2020, is Labor Day. We do NOT have school on MONDAY.

Enjoy the long weekend.

post_text: YSMCS would like to apologize for all of the confusion on the 2 hour delay this morning. As far as our school policy states, our school does follow Mckeesport Area School District on 2 hour delays and cancellations. Today was an exception to this policy as the McKeesport Area School District announced the 2 hour delay at a very late time. All of our other district buses were already on route to pick up students. This is the reason why Young Scholars chose to go forth with a regular schedule. Thank you!
